Text.SourceString: You’re from Pokyo, huh?//<portrait=normal>I came from a metropolitan area myself. The Big Apple… You’ve heard of it, I’m sure.
Anyhow, my name is <NPCName>Scott</>. Welcome to town!//Don’t be a stranger!
Oh man, you reminded me…//I need to drop off some trash at the recycling center today.
Wait, did I offend you? I meant it as a compliment.//<portrait=happy>You look like someone who recycles a lot, for some reason.
I found a couple of empty bottles in the forest yesterday.//<portrait=annoyed>How’d those get there?
Yeah, of course I did.//I brought the bottles and tossed them in the bin on my way home.
Last weekend I walked around town and had lunch on the empty plot of land next to <NpcName>Frank’s</>.
It was nice and quiet.//I could use more of that in my life.
Last weekend I walked around town and had lunch on the empty land next to <NpcName>Frank</>’s.
It was nice and quiet.//I could use more of that in my life.
Time to get back to work.//<portrait=happy>Monday, huh?
Both kinds! We handle artifacts from the cavern and from the sea.//<portrait=normal>They require different approaches to clean.
I love my job.//We get to check out artifacts that have been around for hundreds of years.

Well… It’s not all old. Most of what we get turns out to be junk.//<portrait=normal>But it’s awesome when we get an artifact that’s both rare <Italic>and</> old.//Feels good to be part of the discovery.
What are you up to?//I don’t do much on Tuesdays and Wednesdays.//I usually just go to the museum and then right back to bed.
One of those days, you know?
I like to go to the Tavern to catch up with my crew on the weekend.
I didn’t get to stretch this morning.//<portrait=annoyed>I feel my back tightening up.
I woke up too late again.//Maybe I’ll do some quick stretching later, after work.
I get woken up a lot by weird dreams.//It’s annoying, if you ask me.
I wake up tired, but I can’t ever remember anything. Huh.
You strike me as the type who reads every night before going to bed.//Am I right?
I’m more the light-stretching-before-bed type.
I can’t wait to go to sleep tonight.//Worked out pretty hard this morning… Now I’m all fatigued.
Anything new going on?
I’m feeling tired today.
One thing I’ve noticed about people here is they tend to like wildflowers.//<portrait=normal>Speaking of, though, I’ve heard not everybody likes violets…//So, watch out for that.
I get it. Not a big violet fan myself.
You’re a farmer, right?//Let me ask you something. Is a passion fruit the same as a fig?
I like this place, Coral Island.//It shows there’s more to life than climbing the corporate ladder.
Do you know how to make green smoothies?//Because <NpcName>Alice</> and <NpcName>Suki</> love them.
Yeah, the twins. Wait, you knew they were twins?//<portrait=normal>I couldn’t believe it when I first found out.
I don’t miss the city as much as I thought I would.//<portrait=concerned>There’s not much there for me to miss.
I find all kinds of things in the cavern.//<portrait=annoyed>Some of them are very…weird.
You get so tired after mining all day, yeah.//<portrait=sad>Wow…
I meant me, not you.//Mining just tires me out.//It’s insane!
I’m ready to get back to work! Last weekend was wild.//The people here are so much fun.
Your weekend was fun, I hope?
<NpcName>Frank</> made us one of his experimental recipes last weekend.//<portrait=happy>Heh heh… Wowza! <PlayerName>$player</>, you need to try it. Even just once.
Cross it off your bucket list!
You’re not allergic to moss or anything, right?//<portrait=normal>Because there’s lots of moss around the cavern.
I’d be careful going into the cavern, if I were you.//In case you slip and accidentally get a mouthful of moss.
On my second cup of tea today.
I’m trying to cut back and get my caffeine from tea instead.
I don’t know.//<portrait=sad>Coffee and I just don’t mix.
When I’m cleaning artifacts, I try not to use too much chemical solution because I’m afraid it might damage them.
But some is needed to break through the crust.//So there’s a careful balance we archeologists have to strike.
I think I used too much hair gel today.
Still looks good, though, so I’m not stressed about it.
The cavern in the forest is surprisingly deep.//There are all kinds of things buried down there.
If you’re lucky, you can even find weapons.//<portrait=concerned>Now, how they got there in the first place, nobody knows…
I try to always have my bag with me.//How else am I going to carry everything I find?//<portrait=annoyed>With my bare hands?
Ha ha… What are we? Monsters?
Some of my friends meet up at the community center on Wednesday nights.//They share their feelings and support each other and stuff.//You can join them, if you want to.
Or is it Thursday nights? Hmm…//I don’t remember.
I’m not a weapon kind of guy, so I stick to mining on level 2.
I’ve been practicing with a saber, but it isn’t a one-and-done type of situation, you know?//Maybe one day, when I master it, I’ll dig deeper in the cavern.
I don’t just work at the museum, <PlayerName>$player</>.//I also do my own digging on Thursdays.
Ugh, but I draw the line at digging in Summer.//The cavern’s cool, but it can get too stuffy, if that makes sense.
I don’t just work at the museum, <PlayerName>$player</>.//I also do my own digging on Thursdays.
Ugh, but I draw the line at digging in Summer.//The cavern’s cool, but it can get too stuffy, if that makes sense.
I made the best falafel the other day.//I’m so proud of myself.
I think I used too much hair gel today.
Still looks good, though, right?//I’m not stressed about it.
What a farm you’ve got!
I cut through your farm on my way to the cavern and saw how much work you’ve put in. I have newfound respect for you.
I like working in the field as much as I do in the museum. I’m glad I decided to move here. There are a lot of places to dig.
I tried dating before. Three serious relationships, in fact. I guess I’m not that good at it, because they all crashed and burned.
For a second there, I thought I might be the problem.
But, nah! Can’t be. *laughs* All right, that’s enough psychotherapy for one day.
I’m trying to read this book <NpcName>Millie</> turned me on to. <Italic>The Fairy Tales of Dulca</> or something like that.
I can’t seem to get past the third chapter. You haven’t read it, have you?//I just need to know the gist of it.
Technically, I’m working today. I’m just not in the office.
Right, I don’t work in an office… But you know what I mean.
I just had this epiphany about how little I know about this island.
I keep finding these brand-new pieces of history that make no sense at all. For example, I found a giant spoon at sea one time.
Why would there be this massive cutlery at sea? I’m talking a huge spoon, as big as my head.
Are there, like, giant mermaids or something?
I like <NpcName>Charles</>, but he can be a bit uptight.//Sure, I leave the fridge door open every once in a while, and I’ve accidentally eaten his food, but…
Um… It sounds worse when I say it out loud. Hmm…

I should stop bringing work home with me. It’s caused too many incidents.//This one time, I was cleaning up my geodes in the kitchen. Some dirt must have fallen from them, and it ended up in <NpcName>Charles’s</> burrito…
Man, was he mad at me! Apparently he bit into gravel and almost lost a tooth. I actually felt awful.
Personally, I’m not big on cut flowers. I prefer to enjoy them growing outside.//But what flowers do you like, <PlayerName>$player</>?
You like tulips? I don’t, personally. I don’t know… They just don’t do it for me.
They are pretty, aren’t they? But I can’t have flowers at home. <NpcName>Charles</> won’t stop sneezing if I do.

Special.SourceString: Not a fan of flowers. I’ve tried several… They didn’t taste very good.

Text.SourceString: Another Spring…another year begins…another birthday season for me.//Yep, my birthday’s on the 12th. Two days after the Cherry Blossom Festival.
I’m getting back into my routine now… I can get to the cavern more easily.//The path to the forest isn’t so slippery now the snow’s melted.
I see more and more people outdoors now the weather is <Italic>livable</> again…

One of my worst heartbreaks happened in Spring… It was in the second grade.//We were in the same class. She rejected the worm I found outside and went to play on the monkey bars with Aiden… I wonder how that guy’s doing now…
I did a new workout regimen for Winter.//It was a fifteen-day thing. Can you tell?
I like having breakfast outdoors while looking at the flowers.//Something about it… Especially Spring flowers.
If you’re okay with humidity, you should visit the cavern in Summer.//It’s usually pretty cool inside.
I don’t know if it’s the Summer heat, or… I don’t know what, but one of the shafts in the cavern is so hot lately.//Weird thing is it’s just that one, though… Like something is flaming inside.
My cavern-o-meter isn’t a fancy one, but it picked up the different temperatures in the shafts.//It’s weird. You see, temperatures down there don’t usually change like that.//Even in Summer!
Better soak up the last of that Summer sun, <PlayerName>$player</>.
I’m ready to soak up the sun!//<portrait=annoyed>And if you’re going to remind me about sunscreen, don’t worry. I get an earful every day from <NPCName>Charles</>.//Sunscreen, sunscreen, sunscreen…
I want to play volleyball tomorrow at the beach. I wonder if anybody’ll be there to play with me.//<portrait=concerned><NPCName>Chaem</> maybe? Or…//<portrait=normal>Will you be there?
I don’t mind the walk to the forest, especially on nice Summer days.//I get to see what <NPCName>Dinda’s</> planting, see what <NPCName>Joko’s</> up to. All that stuff.
Don’t you think jazz is the perfect background music for Fall?//Love jazz. It’s the best music… Smooth and all that.
The ground in Fall feels a bit different from other seasons. That’s the first thing I notice, usually.//That and the leaves changing color.
There are so many mushrooms in the forest now.//I don’t do that kind of thing, but if you like them, you should go forage around.
*singing* Mmm shoopadoo wawa hmmmm~
Oh, sorry, <PlayerName>$player</>. I just had this jazz melody in my head.
I live by the water. It’s nice and cool in the morning.
The air in the cavern is much warmer than outside, especially with the snow everywhere.//Rocks are great insulators. Caverns stay relatively the same temperature year round.
Cool when it’s Summer, warm in Winter… That sort of thing.
Remember to be extra careful walking to the forest. Icy path and all.
It’s Winter again. Time does fly when you’re having fun!
Lots of animals hibernate in Winter… Ever wonder which ones hibernate in the caverns?
Having breakfast outdoors is different in Winter… Do not recommend it.
The mayor came by the library the other day and told us a drilling corporation is moving into town.
The Catfish Corp, I think?
Oh, yeah! Pufferfish Corp! There you go.//<portrait=annoyed>Fitting name, don’t you think?
Phew! That New Year’s Eve dinner was unreal!//<portrait=happy>So many fruit pies to choose from.
Have you started working on your farm yet?//There must be a lot of weeding to do.
I’m so sore. I’ve been lifting a lot lately.
Can you tell?
My Summer didn’t start out great, but thanks for asking.//<portrait=normal>How’s your Summer so far?
Aww, me too… I woke up yesterday with bug bites on my ankles.//<portrait=angry>My ankles, <PlayerName>$player</>!
I grew up fishing with my dad. We would wake up early on the weekend, around 4 am, and catch a boat to go fishing at sea.
We’d bring our lunches out and sail home at sunset. Then Dad and I would stop by a ramen place on the way home for dinner. We’d cook up our catch the next day.
I feel sticky… Yuck.
Oh, I’m not too worried about mosquitoes. They prefer one particular blood type over the other.//And mine happens to be “the other.”
The cavern is wild, though. The mosquitos attack no matter what… Maybe because there are no other targets down there.
I don’t know how long my hair can survive in this heat.
I have these holes in my shoes that keep my feet nice and cool.
Have you got those holes in your shoes?
Do you know this song? For some reason it’s been stuck in my head. It goes…
*singing* Dooo doo doo dooo doo dooooo…
Did you catch the melody, <PlayerName>$player</>? I forget what it’s called.
Not many plants can survive the Winter snow. I hope it means less work for you.
Maybe you can bring us some more of those artifacts from the cavern.
In less than three weeks, it’ll be the New Year. I’m psyched!
I need to make sure to stock up on tea.
Hmm… I’m going straight home after work.
I guess I’ll just heat up yesterday’s leftover tacos for dinner.
I hope they’re still good. Hmm…
When it isn’t raining, I like to spend my weekends drinking coffee in front of the house.//You know, doing some people watching.
I figure I’ll stay inside today.//I’m trying not to get too much mud in the house.
The thunder woke me up at two o’clock this morning!
I couldn’t go back to bed after that.
Hmm… I’m going straight home after work.
Hmm… I’m going straight home after work.
Another year has passed.
There are things I wish I’d handled differently.
Friends are important to me.//So I try my best to set aside some time every week to keep up with them.
It may sound crazy, but I think it’s incredible to be working on these artifacts.//I think of it as interacting with our ancestors. Because I kind of am.//The artifacts take me back in time.
Like a time-travel portal! A glimpse of what life was like… A quick look at how the world was hundreds of years ago.
Some of the artifacts here are ones I found.//A small contribution, but it feels good to give back to the field I’m passionate about.
Be part of the history, yeah?
If you think about it, these artifacts and fossils right here are like silent witnesses.//They’ve seen things, <PlayerName>$player</>, that you and I have never even thought about.
And these artifacts know things you and I will never figure out.
Well, of course I know some of it… But yeah.
*mumbling to himself* Is it <NpcName>Frank</> or Rank?
You freaked me out. Say hi next time, will you?
I’m so sore… I’ve been lifting a lot lately.
A nice hot bath sounds excellent right about now.
I had a full day today… I think I deserve to unwind a bit before heading home.
One more over here, <NpcName>Frank</>!
What a great way to end the week.
Do you come here often? I do.//The food’s good, and it’s close to the house and my work.
Besides, listening to <NpcName>Frank</> is better than TV.
Hey, <NpcName>Frank</>! I want to make sure you heard what I just said!
I’m not stressed about growing old. But to be honest, I’m kind of worried I might have to do it alone.
I know I complain about <NpcName>Charles</> sometimes, but I’ll miss him if he ever decides to move on.
I’m brushing up on my fishing.//Just a little hobby I like to do in my spare time.
I just don’t have time to make my own bait.//<portrait=concerned>Besides, <NpcName>Charles</> gets cranky when I start making a mess at the house.
Are you out to go fishing too, <PlayerName>$player</>?
One time, I caught myself a couple of pink snappers within ten minutes of each other.//I’m still amazed about it to this day.
Fingers crossed, <PlayerName>$player</>. It might happen again!
Growing up, Dad would wake me up early on the weekend to go fishing at sea… At around 4 am.
We would bring our lunches out and sail home at sunset.//Then Dad and I would stop by a ramen place on the way home for dinner.//We’d cook up our catch the next day.
I smell like the ocean.
Salty.
Did you bring vitamins with you?
I’m not a weapon kind of guy, so I limit my mining to level 2.
But I still wear armor, you know… Just in case.
I think I’ll go out for a bit and have a snack by the creek.
Whoa!
I didn’t hear you. This cavern can get a bit creepy.
Ah, I didn’t get anything valuable today.
But at least I got a good workout in the cavern.
This is a nice spot for a lunch break.//I might cool my feet in the creek afterward.
Yikes! Something came at me in the dark, so I ran as fast as I could.
I’m still trying to catch my breath.
Did you hear what happened at the Tavern last week?//<portrait=normal>It was wild. <NPCName>Pablo</> did a cartwheel off the counter, and everyone cheered.
You gotta come hang out with us one night.//It’ll be the time of your life, I promise!
I’m pretty sure no one’s beaten my mini golf score yet.//<portrait=happy>Think you’re up for the challenge?
What’s your favorite thing to eat around here?//<portrait=concerned>I’m starving.
I know there’s tons of fresh veggies and stuff, but sometimes you just really want fast food, you know?
There’s so much cool stuff in the cavern, but no one likes to get their hands dirty down there.//It’s too bad.//<portrait=happy>More for me, I guess!
Do you think the town would let me start a cornhole festival?//<portrait=happy>Probably not. I’d win every year.
I should start a Coral Island singles club.//We could all live in the same house and throw big parties and invite other singles.
I did that in college, and it was awesome.//<portrait=normal>Gah, I miss those days.
Between working in the cavern and hanging out, I hardly get any time to myself these days.
They should play more jazz at the Tavern.//<portrait=blushing>It would give it that classy, ritzy feel. Know what I mean?
I kinda feel bad for <NPCName>Suki</>.//<portrait=concerned>She seems to be doing well with her ex, but she still had to go through a divorce.
Can’t get divorced if you don’t get married! That’s my philosophy.
Do you think the town would let me start a cornhole festival?//<portrait=happy>Probably not. I’d win every year.
I’m pretty sure no one’s beaten my mini golf score yet.//<portrait=happy>Think you’re up for the challenge?
I’ve seen people around here pull in some pretty big fish from the ocean.//<portrait=concerned> Makes me wonder what else you could find down there.
I should probably be quiet when I get home tonight.//<portrait=annoyed>Last week <NPCName>Charles</> got mad. Apparently I was “too loud” coming in.
It’s not my fault <NPCName>Charles</> was in bed at 11 pm on a Friday.
There’s nothing better than okra and turnips. They remind me of my mom’s cooking.
Mom always made sure the fridge was stocked with food and snacks and whatever.//<portrait=happy>What a champ!
Between working in the cavern and hanging out, I hardly get any time to myself these days.
I’ve seen people around here pull in some pretty big fish from the ocean.//<portrait=concerned> Makes me wonder what else you could find down there.
I heard some people at the Tavern say they like swimming in the ocean, which is awesome! Lots to see down there, I’m sure.//<portrait=happy>Me? I’m more of a forest guy myself.
They need some new drink recipes down at the Tavern.//<portrait=concerned>I wonder if there’s anything they could make with turnips and okra.
I’d call it the Scott Seltzer!//<portrait=normal>That has a nice ring to it, right?
I went to this one party in college where everything was decorated in gold.//<portrait=annoyed>Not just a gold color, but actual, legit gold.
It was cool. Definitely one of those once-in-a-lifetime experiences.
I’ve tried to get <NPCName>Charles</> a date, but I struck out.//He just wants to sit at the bar and give unsolicited medical advice…//<portrait=annoyed>He’s never going to find a partner like that.
I don’t really miss the city.//The sunsets here are much nicer… In the city, all the buildings block your view of the sky.
Have you seen the stuff <NPCName>Ben</> has in his caravan?//He finds some neat things sometimes.
He found a gold necklace once and put it on his duck.//<portrait=happy>What a guy!
Since you’re here, let me ask you a question.//<portrait=concerned>What’s the best way to fold a shirt?
I remember my mom telling me once, but I totally wasn’t paying attention.//Hmm…
I’ve been seeing a lot of you recently. You sure do get around, don’t you?//<portrait=happy>It’s kind of nice.
Find me next time you’re at the Tavern, and I’ll have <NPCName>Frank</> fix you up something special.//<portrait=happy>Or better yet, I can fix it up!
People like to get married in Spring, don’t they?//<portrait=annoyed>Why would you want to get married with all this pollen in the air?
Might as well just put it off…forever.//<portrait=happy>Ha ha!
It’s finally warm!//<portrait=normal>I would say I can go back to wearing shorts again, but I’ve actually been wearing them all Winter.
I don’t really get cold, I guess.//<portrait=concerned>I guess I’m just <Italic>that</> hot.//<portrait=happy>Ha ha! Just kidding!
The Spring rains erode the cavern a little more each year. Over time, more artifacts and gems are uncovered.//<portrait=happy>Don’t quote me on that, though. That’s just my theory!

There are bad things about rain too, if you think about it.//<portrait=annoyed>For one, if you don’t get to the artifacts in time, the rain can give them a beating. Heck, even destroy them!//<portrait=happy>That’s also my theory.
Are you growing anything new this year, <PlayerName>$player</>?//A big turnip and okra salad sounds delicious right about now.
They say the biggest fish come out in Summer.//You wanna see if I can catch any monsters down at the pier?
The one thing Coral Island has over the city is beach life.//There’s nothing like blasting a cannonball right into the waves.
I can’t believe it’s already Summer.//Sure feels like Winter was just a couple of days ago.
I love Summer! The sun is shining, the weather is warm, and there’s nothing better than hanging out at the beach.
I could go on and on about how much I love Summer, but I think you get the idea.//<portrait=normal>It’s just the best season. Swimsuit every day!
Fall is the time of year when people get into relationships, right?//So they can meet each other’s families during the holidays.
I used to date this girl who loved Fall.//She liked to jump in big piles of leaves and carve pumpkins.
I wonder if there are big leaf piles where she is now.
Am I ready for Winter?//<portrait=normal>Hmm… I guess so.
Fall is the perfect time of year for some good jazz.//<portrait=blushing>Don’t the falling leaves and the crisp breeze make you think of saxophones and trombones?
I need to tell <NPCName>Charles</> to turn the heat up in the house.//It’s really starting to get cold out here.
Is it just me, or does Winter seem like the quietest season?//<portrait=normal>Someone needs to turn up the volume out here.
Winter just seems so depressing to me. It’s dark and cold, and everything is dead.
I heard <NPCName>Kenny</> say at the ranch that you gotta keep your animals inside during Winter.//Is it true?
I guess you don’t want your milk and eggs to come out frozen.
Give me sunshine and a swimsuit any day over snow and a parka.
I think I’ll actually have to wear long pants when I go digging now.//The cavern’s all right this time of year, but it’s freezing on the walk over there.
Everyone on the island seems to like Winter the most, but I’m really more of a Summer guy.//<portrait=happy>What’s not to love about sweating it out on the beach?
I know some people hate the rain, but I actually like it.//It’s like a natural lullaby.
Rain isn’t too bad. It makes everything look hazy…like a dream.//<portrait=concerned>It <Italic>does</> make my hair go all frizzy, though. It’s like I’m stuck in a bad ’80s music video.
Coral Island has more rain than any island I’ve ever been to.
Oh, I’ve been to plenty of islands!//<portrait=normal>I’ve been around, you know. What’s the point of being young if you don’t travel?
Jeez, I can’t even get fresh air out here without taking in a mouthful of water.//<portrait=concerned>Is this how fish feel?
Jeez, I can’t even get fresh air out here without taking in a mouthful of water.//<portrait=concerned>Is this how fish feel?
Hello? Is that you, <PlayerName>$player</>? I can hear you, but I can’t see through all this rain!
I need to cover up my artifacts.//<portrait=sad>Or else all the humidity is going to make them rust.
The rain is really coming down out there. I hope it doesn’t ruin your plans for the day.
I can’t believe it’s raining again. I thought we were supposed to have nice weather this weekend.
I was going to go down to the pier today, but the rain wouldn’t let up.//<portrait=happy>Oh well! At least I get to see you.
Don’t the big fish come out when it’s raining?//<portrait=happy>I wanna go catch some, but…I’m too lazy.
Rainy days make me feel like curling up with some tea and reading a book… And I don’t even like to read.//<portrait=happy>Weird, isn’t it?
Think you could surf in weather like this?//<portrait=happy>I bet the waves would be, like, higher than my house.
It better not be raining again tomorrow.//I’ve got things to do.
I hate going into the cavern on days like this.//<portrait=annoyed>Hearing thunder while you’re deep in a cavern tunnel is just too creepy.
<NPCName>Charles</> hates when it storms at night. He says he’s worried something will fall on the house.//Worries too much, that one.
I remember this drink my buddies and I came up with, called Stormy Night.//<portrait=happy>Every sip made you roar like a storm!//<portrait=normal>Wanna try it sometime?
I remember this drink my buddies and I came up with, called Stormy Night.//<portrait=happy>Every sip made you roar like the storm!//<portrait=normal>Wanna try it sometime?
Snow day!
The snow makes my hair go flat.//Do you think it looks flat?//<portrait=normal>Phew! Don’t worry about yours. Your hair always looks great!
Gold was so valuable in the ancient world.//If they wanted to remember something, they usually immortalized it in gold.
It turns out that when something’s rare, that makes it more valuable.
Here’s a weird question for you.//If you’d lived thousands of years ago, what would you want to leave behind for people to remember you by?

Oh, that’s neat! For me, I think I’d want to keep a notebook.//<portrait=happy>That way, I could tell future generations what life was like when I was around.//<portrait=normal>It doesn’t really matter, though, since I’m here now.
Welcome to party central! Make yourself at home.//<portrait=normal><NPCName>Charles</> might disagree with that characterization, but hey!

I know what you’re thinking, you know. “What’s that sweet sound? And why does it make me feel so happy and relaxed?”//<portrait=normal>It’s none other than the smoothest of smooth jazz, presented by yours truly.
I keep it going all the time… Sometimes even overnight.
Rock climbing? Here?//<portrait=concerned>Hmm… I guess you could, if you really wanted to.//<portrait=annoyed>I don’t recommend it, though.
Honestly, rock climbing is pretty good preparation for working in a cavern.//<portrait=sad>But it does seem dangerous to do it here.
Okay, I have a joke for you. I’ve been wanting to tell you this one ever since I first saw you come into the cavern.
What did the miner say when he walked into the cavern? //<portrait=happy>He said, “Wow, this place <Italic>rocks</>!”//Where’re the laughs?
Let’s get some more drinks going in here! Next round’s on me!
The music is always bumping, and there’s a great selection of drinks and snacks here.
Stay tuned, <PlayerName>$player</>. I’m gonna do something cool soon!//<portrait=normal>I just don’t know what.
You might not know this, but I was captain of the billiards team when I was in college.//<portrait=normal>Not to brag, but they called me <NPCName>Scott</> the Pool Master.
Is there any way to tell if the big fish are out today? They should do a Coral Island fish forecast.
If I could just catch a red king arowana one of these days, I’d be a happy man.
I keep asking for one for my birthday, but no one around here seems to be able to catch one, either.
Hey, <PlayerName>$player</>! You and I should have a fishing competition one day. We can see who catches the biggest fish.
Honestly, I’d rather be lifting weights or jogging, but yoga’s cool too.
Anything that gets me moving is cool with me.
I make a lot of assumptions about people.//I mean, most of the time, I turn out to be right, but I feel like I should stop.
People don’t like it when I do that.
You’re pretty cool for a farmer, <PlayerName>$player</>. Heh heh.
Teasing… You’re pretty cool, <Italic>period</>.
I feel bad sometimes when I go home and see <NpcName>Charles</> eating alone…//<portrait=sad>He doesn’t really get any visitors.
Okay, neither do I. That is a fair point, but something about <NpcName>Charles</> is different…
I haven’t personally worked with <NpcName>Zarah</>, but she did donate some of the valuable artifacts at the museum.
I often run into her in the forest.//I think she knows a lot more about this island than most of us.
Strange, there was a kite just outside my window this morning.
I haven’t seen anyone flying a kite in ages.
I ran into a monster in the cavern the other day and somehow managed to kill it.//<NpcName>Kira</> actually gave me a bounty for it! I wonder if I can do it again?
I’m not giving up, though. After all, I’m down in the cavern anyway. Why not make the most of it?

Bleh… I had some fresh veggies yesterday, and I can still taste the bitter flavor on my tongue.//<portrait=annoyed>Vegetables aren’t for me. So when I go down in the cavern, I usually just pack vitamins from the clinic.
Okra’s all right, though.
You’re so chill, like wow!
Very cool. You need to teach me how to be cool like you one of these days!
It might not be a bad idea to move out of <NpcName>Charles’s</> and stay at the inn.//<portrait=normal>Could be a refreshing change of scenery.
But that’s probably just my weekend brain talking.//<portrait=happy>Who am I kidding? Nothing beats living ten minutes away from work.

I’ve been making fake files and slipping them into <NpcName>Charles’s</> work files.//<portrait=normal>I made fake patient files with phony illnesses, like unicorn headaches. I wonder if he’ll catch on. Ha ha!
You’re right. I do have too much time on my hands.
You know what, <PlayerName>$player</>? You’re a cool, fun person.//We need to hang out more.
Ha ha… That was random. But I just thought you should know.
I hope you don’t think I’m a clown or anything.//I know I can be full of it sometimes, but trust me, there’s more to me than that.
I care what you think of me.
I’m not stressed about growing old. But… I’m kind of worried I might have to do it alone.
I know I complain about <NpcName>Charles</> sometimes, but I’d miss him if he ever decided to move on.//<portrait=concerned>I should stop trolling him…//<portrait=happy>Nah! Ha ha ha!
You sure know how to work the room, huh?//You killed it at that party with <NpcName>Pablo</> and my friends.
That’s it, <PlayerName>$player</>! From now on, I’m taking you to all my parties.
I’ve thought about changing my hair a couple of times, but I have no idea how to settle on a style.
Maybe I could try a buzz cut like <NpcName>Sam</>.//<portrait=normal>It looks good on him, don’t you think? And I’d save a ton on hair gel.
Do you think about the future much, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Yeah, that’s why I prefer to live in the moment. We have a lot in common.

Special.SourceString: Yeah, it gets overwhelming after a while.

Text.SourceString: You know, I couldn’t stop thinking about you last night. Umm…

Special.SourceString: More than ever, lately… And you’re in it.

Text.SourceString: Hear, hear!

Special.SourceString: No. Live in the moment, Scott.

Text.SourceString: If you’re ever feeling down, remember this: everyone’s good at something.//If you haven’t figured out what that is, keep looking, because it’s out there.
Phew! Me, sharing wisdom! That was weird.//<portrait=normal>I guess living with <NpcName>Charles</> has had an effect on me…a good one, it seems.
I wish I’d spent the weekend with you instead. It was good, but I know it could’ve been better.
It’s impossible to be bored when I’m hanging out with you… Hear me? Impossible.
Well… We all need money, but all joking aside, <PlayerName>$player</>, don’t take life too seriously. Remember to breathe a little.
I should really cut my hair, huh?//It seems like the Summer heat bewitches my hair and makes it grow extra fast.
It must get lonely up there at the farm…alone.//<portrait=happy>If you want some company, drop by the house anytime…
You’re always welcome at my place.
I think I ate something bad this morning.
My stomach won’t stop growling. Hmm…
I don’t want to show up at your place unannounced. I know you value your privacy, and I like that about you.//<portrait=blushing>But please don’t think I don’t want to.
Just wanted to clear that up…
The system at the museum was down the other day. Thankfully, <NpcName>Lily</> was able to stop by and help out.
I could have tried to fix it, I guess.//<portrait=happy>But I didn’t know how… Ha ha!
I’m liking that shirt on you, <PlayerName>$player</>!
Maybe I’d look good in that color too. I might try it out.
I was thinking about you last night.//I had my warm milk in bed, and of all a sudden, I remembered the first time I saw you…that Spring, remember?
I thought you were really cute, and you seemed cool from the start.//<portrait=blushing>The rest was just you proving me right.
The rain makes everything feel so fresh and clean. I love the smell of wet pavement and leaves.
What did you do today, <PlayerName>$player</>?//<portrait=sad>You seem a little tired. Is it the weather?
It seems like the perfect weather for snuggling, don’t you think?
I was just thinking about you.
Go somewhere and warm up, <PlayerName>$player</>. You look like you’re freezing.
Don’t get sick, okay?
Sometimes, I wish I’d been born a hundred years ago, when men still wore suits everywhere and jazz was the big thing.
Technology is cool and all, but nothing beats a good big-band show.
I’ve been working out extra lately. Can you tell?

Would you help me pick out an artifact to send back to my mom sometime?//No pressure or anything. I just think you two have the same taste.//<portrait=blushing> She’d probably love anything you pick out.
Days like this are perfect for cuddling on the sofa with someone special.//<portrait=blushing>Interested, <PlayerName>$player</>?
We can… If you want to.
It’s nice and toasty here. In the mood for something hot?//<portrait=surprised02>To drink, I mean!
Everyone stay close in here so we can keep warm!//<portrait=blushing>And also so I don’t have to shout.
Speaking of… You smell really nice up close, <PlayerName>$player</>.//This is the best part about snowy days…

I don’t think I’ll ever be a fan of cold Winters, but I guess that’s just how it goes. Some people love them, and some people don’t.//<portrait=blushing>I wouldn’t mind if…if someone had to keep my hands warm.
This would be an excellent place for a date, you know.//Just you, me, and thousands of years of history all around us.
I’ve never met anyone else who likes the cavern as much as I do.//<portrait=concerned><NPCName>Zarah’s</> down here a lot, but she’s looking for adventure, not treasure.
It’s nice… We have lots in common.
I swear, I <Italic>knew</> I’d run into you here.//<portrait=normal>Odd, isn’t it?
I always have a great time here, but we need some new stuff on the menu.//Maybe I should tell <NPCName>Frank</> about that okra and turnip drink I came up with.
I don’t know about you, but I’m counting down the days until Summer is finally here.
There’s just something about holding an artifact in your hands and imagining all the people and events it’s seen.
I think artifacts are an incredible way to connect with the past and gain a deeper understanding of the world we live in. Agree?
I don’t know about you, but I could spend hours in a museum looking at artifacts and learning about their history.
If you haven’t tried Frank’s mystery dish yet, you’re definitely missing out. It’s an experience you won’t forget.
The weather is so dreary and depressing today. It’s just not my thing.
